PLANTS OF SOUTH CAROLINA
SUMTER COUNTY

*GALAX APHYLLA* L.

No fruiting stalks seen; small population on
steep dry bluff on S side of Tavern Creek,
where many outcrops of Fuller's earth occur;
below thick layer of *Kalmia latifolia*; about
100 m E of Milford Plantation road; W side of
Manchester State Forest.

John B. Nelson 4120
with S. Bennett, A. Rome        18 July 1985

SOUTH CAROLINA HERITAGE TRUST PROGRAM
